full_text: Users with the user admin privileges can manage users and groups. Log in as SuperUser. Click the Administration tab. Select Users and Security. The internal organization Enigma Fire and Casualty is always displayed by default. Organizations have groups and subgroups. Click a group, for example, Eastern Region. Group information. Group information is located on different tabs. The Basics tab contains the group name, parent group, organization information, security zone, etc. The Users tab lists the users belonging to this group. Users can be added and removed through this tab. The Producer Codes tab lists all producer codes available to the parent group which can be made available in the current group by setting it to Yes in the Available column. The Queues tab lists the queues used for activity assignment assignment. The Regions tab. The Regions tab lists the regions that the system uses for making assignment decisions. To search for a group, go to the Groups page under Users and Security in the left menu. For example, let's find the group for Los Angeles producers in the Armstrong organization. You can enter any free text or a partial word. Click Search. Click the desired group to view the details. Clicking the organization's link on the Basic tab takes you to the organization's detail page. After examining the organization's groups, the user admin decides to add a new group for foster city producers. Click Actions. Select New Group. Enter the group name. The new group belongs to the organization Armstrong and Company. Click the search icon. Enter the search criteria. Click Search. Select the right organization. Set producer as the type of the new group. The security zone applies restriction on internal users when they are searching for other users, groups, producer codes, or organizations. The internal user must have the same security zone as on the group to access the group. Select Western Region. Select localization. Click Update to save the new group.  The search word is pretext. Click Search. Click the user link in the result list. The basic step lists information about the user regarding internal or external, user type, etc. The Attributes tab can be used to associate custom attributes with the user for assignment purpose. Some examples of user attributes are expertise, language, line of business. The Access tab lists the groups the user belongs to, and producer codes if user producer code security is set to yes. Manage the roles of the user on the Roles tab. In this example, Alice Applegate has two roles, Underwriter and Reinsurance Manager. The Profiles tab displays the basic information about the user. The Regions tab is used to add the geographic area for the user. The UW Authority tab lists the underwriting authority profiles used to approve underwriting issues. Let's add a new user to the group created earlier. Click Actions. Select New User. Enter the user's information. Enter the user's information. Enter name. To set a user as an external user, set External to Yes. The user belongs to Armstrong and Company. Click the search icon. Enter name. Click Search. Select the organization. Set the user type to be Producer. Enter a phone number. Click Update to save the new user. The warning messages are displayed about non-matching roles and group. Go to the Roles tab. Add the Producer role. Enter the producer role. Go to the Access tab. In the Groups section, click Add. Select User Group. Select Foster City Producers, the group created earlier. Note that the User Producer Code security is set to Yes. Users inherit Producer codes from their group, and can have additional codes added. Click Update again. The user has been created successfully. Click Update.
